ite of innovation-related services, capabilities, and global connectivity. These can be individually tailored to meet your needs or provided through an integrated <strong>Sponsored Invention</strong> engagement.\r\n\r\nFrom initial collaboration, defining challenges and industry opportunities, to our solution innovation and business development support, IDF will work as your innovation partner, fully invested in mutual success.[/vc_column_text][vc_tta_tour][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" title=\"Opportunities &amp; Strategy\" tab_id=\"1441142697616-9772428f-dd1c\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1442865250526{padding-left: 30px !important;}\"]\r\n\r\nIDF’s invention experts will partner with your company’s thought leaders, technologists, and stakeholders to identify your key business and technology challenges. We translate these challenges into innovation opportunities as we work in collaboration to clearly understand the technical landscape, existing solution gaps, and technical needs required for success.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_type=\"linecons\" i_icon_linecons=\"vc_li vc_li-megaphone\" title=\"Co-Invention Session\" tab_id=\"1441142938988-df4098ea-edf7\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nAn IDF <em>Co-Invention Session</em> is the ultimate think tank event – focused entirely on meeting your company’s specific challenges. Based on the technical challenges identified in our initial discussions, we assemble our best experts and spend the day in purposeful creative dialog, capturing all emerging ideas for subsequent evaluation and consideration toward real-world solutions.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_type=\"linecons\" i_icon_linecons=\"vc_li vc_li-settings\" title=\"IP-Minded Consulting\" tab_id=\"1441142697870-b0d00517-aa87\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nWe carefully consider industry trends, technology insights, competitive landscapes, and IP strategy to assist you in creating a roadmap to success. Our highly experienced team will help you evaluate emerging opportunities and design a technology pathway to take advantage of new innovations.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-users\" title=\"Invention Network Solutions\" tab_id=\"1441142981313-aaf03c6e-3a4b\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]The Intellectual Ventures Inventor Network (IVIN) consists of more than 10,000 individual members and 400 represented research institutes and universities located all around the world. Unlike the typical “crowd-source” invention approach, IDF has well-established working relationships with its IVIN members. According to the specific invention need, we call upon the most suitable skillsets to help us seek solutions.\r\n\r\nIVIN inventors may be significant participants in our Inventor Brainstorm Sessions and key responders to our Request For Invention (RFI) process.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-child\" title=\"Request for Invention\" tab_id=\"1441142982681-a311e3b4-3c34\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nTo solicit new ideas from our global inventor network, we send out a Request for Invention (RFI). This unique document clearly defines the specific technical challenge to be solved on behalf of your organization. The content of the RFI is carefully crafted to elicit inventive concepts and to obtain optimal technical solutions on your behalf.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_type=\"openiconic\" i_icon_openiconic=\"vc-oi vc-oi-chart-pie\" title=\"Patent Portfolio Access\" tab_id=\"1441142984157-e3537e79-ac88\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]Fortify your IP position through licensing or acquiring additional assets from IDF’s diverse collection of patents. We have a unique set of patents and invention assets that can complement your existing set of patented innovations.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://inventiondevfund.com/patent-search/\">VIEW PATENTS</a> &gt;[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-globe\" title=\"Global Market Relationships\" tab_id=\"1441142986472-dc3d765b-f9b1\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_column_text]IDF has highly valuable connections in rapidly emerging industries and global markets. Our international relationships can help to accelerate your entry into new markets around the world.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://inventiondevfund.com/portfolio-item/coffee-flour/\">READ OUR CASE STUDY</a> &gt;[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-rocket\" title=\"Sponsored Invention Engagement \" tab_id=\"1442865963750-f8fc0894-6c18\" add_icon=\"true\"][vc_raw_html]\r\n\r\\r\n\r\n[/vc_raw_html][vc_column_text]<em>Sponsored Invention - powerful innovation services delivering highly focused solutions</em>\r\n\r\nTake a look inside our Sponsored Invention solution in the context of just one of the dozens of industries in which we operate. To learn more about how we can support your specific needs, <a href=\"/contact-us/\">let’s talk.</a>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_bottom=\"50\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042786961{margin-bottom: -40px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-color: #8ec549 !important;}\" bg_color=\"#0e73a3\" padding_top=\"50\"][vc_column width=\"3/4\" delimiter=\"vline\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">READY TO START THE CONVERSATION?</span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\" css=\".vc_custom_1440811513097{margin-top: 17px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"LET\'S TALK!\" color=\"custom\" hover_color=\"custom\" size=\"lg\" align=\"center\" shape=\"square\" button_block=\"true\" link=\"url:http%3A%2F%2Finventiondevfund.com%2Fcontact-us%2F||\" custom_color=\"#f78e18\" hover_custom_color=\"#dd9e40\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','IVIDF Services','','publish','open','closed','','services','','','2016-01-07 19:47:10','2016-01-07 19:47:10','',0,'http://demo.olevmedia.net/amax/?page_id=532',0,'page','',0),(636,1,'2015-02-04 06:46:38','2015-02-04 06:46:38','[vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" bg_image_att=\"fixed\" bg_image=\"2481\" padding_top=\"100\" padding_bottom=\"50\" font_color=\"#212121\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 class=\"p1\"><a href=\"http://ividf.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Orange-line.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2682\" src=\"http://ividf.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Orange-line.jpg\" alt=\"Orange-line\" width=\"3\" height=\"49\" /></a>OUR TEAM</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_empty_space][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1426151787824{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2605\" name=\"Chris Alliegro\" job=\"Executive Vice President\" description=\"Chris is the executive vice president for the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures. He has more than 20 years of experience as a scientist, engineer, and businessperson.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Intellectual Ventures, Chris was vice president at the research and advisory firm, Directions on Microsoft, where he covered Microsoft\'s business applications and platform strategies, and advised clients such as SAP and Salesforce.com. He also held several positions at Microsoft including director of data center operations and engineering for Microsoft\'s global information technology group, director of engineering for MSN\'s data centers and test labs, and group program manager for the Commerce Server product development team.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Microsoft, Chris was a member of the technical staff at Bell Laboratories, where he led projects in operations support systems and network design and drove implementation of AT&amp;T local telephony services. Before joining Bell Labs, Chris conducted research in elementary particle physics at Yale University and Brookhaven National Lab.\r\n\r\nChris holds a Ph.D. in physics from Yale University and a bachelor’s degree in physics from the State University of New York at Binghamton.\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2608\" name=\"Patrick Ennis\" job=\"Global Head of Technology\" description=\"Patrick has more than 25 years of experience as a scientist, engineer, businessman, and venture capitalist. In his current role with IDF, he invests in innovation, intellectual property, and technology commercialization worldwide, with a special focus on Asia. He is part of the founding team that built and manages a 10,000 person global invention network.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Intellectual Ventures in 2008, Patrick was a Managing Director of ARCH Venture Partners where he identified, funded and built early stage startups which emanated from universities and national labs in a wide range of markets – especially those involving interdisciplinary technology across software, computing, communications, semiconductors, materials science, energy, life sciences, and other areas.\r\n\r\nBefore joining the venture capital industry in 1998 as a Kauffman Fellow, Patrick held R&amp;D and business positions with Lucent Technologies, AT&amp;T, and Bell Labs. He led engineering projects for software development, speech recognition, network design and operations. He also worked in product management for the optical networking business and marketing where he led new product launches.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Bell Labs in 1992, Patrick conducted research in Nuclear Physics from 1984 to 1992 at universities and national labs in North America and Europe. He published many articles describing his work in scientific journals including The Physical Review, Zeitschrift für Physik, Physics Letters and Nuclear Instruments and Methods. He is an inventor on several patents and has written articles and book chapters on innovation.\r\n\r\nPatrick has served on numerous corporate, educational, and non-profit boards. His current directorships include: Evolv Technology, Benemilk Oy, Ignite Northwest, The W Fund and the Lockheed Martin strategic technical advisory board. He is a frequent invited speaker at conferences.\r\n\r\nHis degrees include: a PhD, MS, and MPhil in Physics from Yale University; an MBA from the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania; and a BS in Mathematics and Physics from the College of William and Mary where he was elected to Phi Beta Kappa.\r\n\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2610\" name=\"Matt Brock\" job=\"Head of Operations\" description=\"Matt is the head of operations for the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures. In this role he oversees the processes and platforms underpinning the business unit, and partners closely with his IDF management colleagues to ensure they have the tools to achieve their objectives. He has held a variety of general management and operational roles throughout Intellectual Ventures since joining as Edward Jung’s Technical Assistant in July 2008, when he participated in the launch of IDF.\r\n\r\nMatt’s 15 year career has taken him through operations management, finance, and marketing roles in a range of businesses and markets, from financial services and renewable energy startups (Asset Exchange; Imperium Renewables) to Fortune 500 companies such as HSBC and GE Commercial Finance. These diverse roles have all been at the right-brain/left-brain interface point where human systems connect with computer and data systems, and that’s where Matt loves to work.\r\n\r\nMatt attended business school at Seattle University, culminating in a MS Finance degree focused on asset pricing and decision science. He also has a B.A. in Philosophy from Reed College.\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2930\" name=\"Michael Day\" job=\"Chief Counsel\" description=\"Michael joined Intellectual Ventures in 2014 as Chief Counsel, Invention Development Fund. He supports invention sourcing, commercialization, and other fund activities.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Intellectual Ventures, Michael held the title of Senior Corporate Counsel-Operations at Amazon, functioning as primary counsel to senior leadership for North American operations and global customer service. Prior to Amazon, he provided transactional and commercial counsel to the Energy and Plastics business units at General Electric. In these roles, he had responsibilities for legal issues pertaining to inorganic growth and business portfolio management, serving as legal lead on domestic and international transactional matters as well as structuring and negotiating various types of commercial arrangements. Michael began his legal career with Skadden Arps in New York, focusing on public and private M&amp;A and financing transactions.\r\n\r\nPrior to law school, Michael was with The Aerospace Corporation as a project engineer where he provided technical advisory services relating to the development, deployment, and operation of national security space systems ‒ including technical analyses, performance requirements, concept design studies, and source-selection evaluations.\r\n\r\nMichael received a bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering from Purdue University, a master’s degree in electrical engineering from the University of Southern California and a law degree from the University of Virginia. He is licensed to appear before the bar in the states of Washington and New York.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1426151787824{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2934\" name=\"Brett Hertzberg\" job=\"Chief IP Counsel\" description=\"Brett joined IDF in 2008, after serving as the managing partner for the Seattle office of Merchant &amp; Gould, a prominent U.S. intellectual property law firm.\r\n\r\nIn managing the Patent Development Group, Brett routinely taps into his prior experience managing attorneys and counseling clients in all aspects of intellectual property.\r\n\r\nForming a collaborative business partnership between the Patent Development Group and the portfolio teams and licensing teams has been a constant focus in Brett’s present practice.\r\n\r\nBrett also has taken a lead role in supervising outside counsel to meet the various business needs of IDF in all aspects of our developing patent portfolio.\r\n\r\nPrior to entering the world of law, Brett worked as a Senior engineer at TLSI, an ASIC design house, and also at the Grumman Aerospace Corporation. While an Engineer, Brett worked on various research and development projects, and supervised the design, manufacture, and testing of digital/analog circuits, systems, and software development. In joining IV, Brett gets to wear the hat of an engineer, lawyer and business leader, utilizing the full breadth of his skills acquired as a lawyer and an engineer.\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2944\" name=\"Paul Levins\" job=\"Program Director, APAC EU Monetization &amp; Country Head, ANZ\" description=\"Paul has over 25 years’ experience in the corporate, government and not for profit sectors. His previous roles include:\r\n\r\nExecutive Officer and Vice President of the Internet Corporation for Assigned names and Number (ICANN), an organisation at the heart of the Internet, setting up ICANN’s Washington DC office and negotiating a new accountability mechanism with the United States Department of Commerce;\r\nChief of Staff and senior adviser in State and Federal portfolios including Health, Forestry, Water, Infrastructure and Natural Resources, Housing, Higher education, Employment Services and Social Security;\r\nSenior executive roles at Infrastructure and telecommunications companies: Bilfinger Berger Australia, Telstra, and Baulderstone Hornibrook.\r\nHe is also an Independent Director of the Board of auDA (the policy authority and industry self-regulatory body for Australia\'s .au domain space); an Independent Director of the ANZAC Medical Research Institute and an Ambassador for Business Events Sydney.\r\n\r\nPaul holds a Bachelor of Arts from Macquarie University, Sydney and is an Honorary Associate, Mentor and Guest lecturer at the Graduate School of Government at the University of Sydney.\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2932\" name=\"Nick Gibson\" job=\"Head of Marketing\" description=\"Nick serves as Head of Marketing for the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures. He is based in Tokyo, Japan and oversees all IDF marketing, communications, and sales enablement activities worldwide.\r\n\r\nNick has worked with IV since the launch of IDF in 2005, when he helped establish both the Japanese and Korean prototype operations for IV’s Asian business expansion. Previous to his current role, Nick held senior positions in business development, product development, and corporate communications at IV.\r\n\r\nPrior to this, Nick was a Director at K2 Services Corporation, an early stage venture capital company investing in and incubating technology companies in Japan, Korea and Singapore.\r\n\r\nNick began his career as a marketing consultant in Tokyo, advising many Fortune 100 companies including Microsoft, Proctor &amp; Gamble, and Citigroup. Nick has a BA from Colgate University in Hamilton, New York. He has lived and worked in Asia since 1996, and is fluent in Japanese.\" readmore=\"Read Bio\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2943\" name=\"Monish Suvarna\" job=\"Head of Product Development\" description=\"Monish is Head of Product Development at Intellectual Ventures’ Invention Development Fund (IDF). Before that he held the role of President at Intellectual Ventures India. Intellectual Ventures India’s goal is to make invention an important activity in the Indian economy by partnering with Indian institutions to build an innovation ecosystem that works in the Indian environment.\r\n\r\nMonish was part of the founding team of the IDF. He also started IDF’s operations in India. He has 20 years’ experience working as a computer scientist and entrepreneur in both India and the United States.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Intellectual Ventures in 2006, Monish held many roles as an entrepreneur in Silicon Valley. He was a Senior Director of Data Robotics where he was part of the founding team.\r\n\r\nBefore Data Robotics, Monish was at BlueArc Corporation, a startup building the world’s fastest data servers, where he was responsible for building the data storage component of the MCR supercomputer at Lawrence Livermore National Labs (the third fastest supercomputer at that time).\r\n\r\nMonish was the Chief Architect at Centigram Communications and continued in that role after Centigram Communications was acquired by ADC Telecom. While there, he designed speech technology products including a text to speech engine used by Dr. Stephen Hawking.\r\n\r\nMonish is a Sloan Fellow from the Stanford Graduate School of Business. He also received a Master’s degree in Computer Science from the University of California, Santa Barbara and a Bachelor of Engineering degree in Electronics and Communication Engineering from the National Institute of Technology.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1426151787824{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2940\" name=\"Masanobu Katoh\" job=\"Country Head, Japan\" description=\"Katoh is executive director and country head of the Intellectual Ventures’ office in Japan.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Intellectual Ventures, Katoh served in several positions with Fujitsu in Japan, where he was ultimately appointed as Executive Vice President of the Fujitsu Research Institute. His previous roles with Fujitsu included Corporate Vice President and managing the company’s intellectual property and legal groups, chairman and CEO of Fujitsu Management Services America, and Senior Vice President of Fujitsu Laboratories.\r\n\r\nFrom the time he worked for Fujitsu, Katoh was actively involved in policy and regulatory discussions regarding the Internet and digital society, and was chairman of the Internet Law &amp; Policy Forum (ILPF), a board member for the Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers (ICANN), and chairman for the electronic commerce committee of the Global Information Infrastructure Commission (GIIC).\r\n\r\nKatoh received his bachelor’s degree in law from the University of Tokyo and his master’s degree in law from the University of Michigan Law School. He has also been appointed as a special research professor at Keio University. He is licensed to appear before the bar in Washington, D.C. and New York.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2960\" name=\"Yan Sheng\" job=\"Country Head, China\" description=\"YS heads up the China office for Intellectual Ventures.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining IV, YS had a long and distinguished career in banking and finance with some of the world’s leading financial institutions. His experience includes Bank of China in FICC business, Lehman Brothers in Fixed Income, FleetBoston as MD and Head of Greater China, and most recently he worked at AIG Financial Product as MD and Head of China. He has also worked with other prominent firms including Tokyo Mitsubishi Intl, Commonwealth Bank Australia, and South Africa based Standard Bank.\r\n\r\nAltogether, YS has about 30 years’ experience in Asia, New York, and Europe working in investment banking and fund management. His expertise includes management, fund-raising, sales and trading, investment strategy, and corporate advisory.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2954\" name=\"David Drake\" job=\"Country Head, Singapore and Korea\" description=\"David is the Country head of Singapore and Korea and is responsible for driving strategic alliances with corporations and government entities based in Southeast Asia and Korea.\r\n\r\nThe goal is to create partnerships with companies to develop and commercialize IV’s intellectual properties and to get them into various industries to generate revenue for its investors. He brings over 30 years of experience in investment banking, private equity, and M&amp;A to IV.\r\n\r\nHe started working with IV in 2009 and is based out of IV’s Singapore office. Prior to IV, David founded and ran a $300M private equity fund focused on the Asian markets. He also worked at Merrill Lynch as the Managing Director in charge of Global Principal Investments–Japan, and held similar positions at the Bank of America and General Electric Capital. During his tenure in Asia, spanning nearly 17years, he has personally led businesses that have invested in excess of $3.5Bn in Asia.\r\n\r\nDavid’s career in banking began in Chicago after receiving his MBA from Washington University in St. Louis in 1984. David holds a B.A. in business and history from Coe College of Cedar Rapids, Iowa.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2959\" name=\"Parminder Singh\" job=\"Country Head, Canada &amp; Program Director, Enterprise Programs\" description=\"Par has more than 25 years of professional experience in building, operating, and managing international businesses for private companies, government clients, and multinational corporations around the world.\r\n\r\nPar is currently the President of Intellectual Ventures Canada. In addition to the overall management of the Canadian operation, Par is responsible for establishing partnerships with a network of Inventors from start-up companies, academia, government agencies and general industry. Collectively, these groups of Inventors create commercially viable solutions in areas of Physical Science, Life Sciences and Information Technology.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Intellectual Ventures, Par was the Managing Director of the Microsoft Canada Development Center (MCDC), located in Richmond, British Columbia. Par was responsible for establishing the Center and setting its strategic direction. Today, the Centre is one of the premier software development locations for Microsoft. Par also served as the Director of Business Development and the General Manager for Xbox where he provided strategic direction, developed go-to-market strategies, and led negotiations with major manufacturing and content partners.\r\n\r\nDuring his career Par spent 15 years designing, constructing and launching communications and broadcast satellites systems for private companies and governments around the world. He also found time to establish three successful start-up companies that focused on the areas of multimedia, internet software tools development and electronics manufacturing.\r\n\r\nPar has held executive positions at companies in Canada and US including: Ensequence, Telesat Canada, Motorola, Teledisc, Microsoft, FreeInternet Networks, and 5th Link Software. Additionally, he has consulted for numerous companies including: Boeing, Acer, ATT, Flextronics, Wistron, Hughes Aircraft Company, Space Systems/Loral, Nortel, and Bell Northern Research.\r\n\r\nPar sits on the Board of Directors of Junior Achievement of British Columbia and DigiBC. He holds a Bachelor\'s degree in Electrical Engineering from the Technical University of Nova Scotia and lives in Surrey, British Columbia, Canada and is married with three children, a dog, and an occasional goldfish.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1426151787824{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2939\" name=\"Ken Poppe\" job=\"Country Head, North America\" description=\"Ken is U.S. Country Head for the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures. Ken joined Intellectual Ventures in 2007 and he was initially responsible for directing the fund’s financial strategy and overseeing investor relations. In the fall of 2011, he moved into his current role where he manages U.S. university relationships and supports IP monetization initiatives.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Intellectual Ventures, Ken spent eleven years at Starbucks, where he led post-acquisition corporate integrations, helped introduce the Starbucks Card program in the U.S. and later led the Card’s launch in Europe, and held various finance positions. Prior to Starbucks, Ken was vice president of credit and operations for Lease Management Services, Inc., a Menlo Park, Calif.-based venture debt financing subsidiary of Sumitomo Corporation of America. Earlier in his career, he served as a senior analyst for Continental Airlines, Inc., and worked in public accounting at Arthur Young &amp; Co.\r\n\r\nKen earned his MBA from the Stern School of Business at New York University and his bachelor’s degree in business administration from Washington State University. He is a certified public accountant in the state of Washington.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2961\" name=\"Jeri Andrews\" job=\"Head of North America Sales\" description=\"As Head of North America Sales, Jeri is responsible for commercialization efforts within the Invention Development Fund.\r\n\r\nSince joining Intellectual Ventures in 2014, she has been responsible for the holistic management of several key client relationships, many of which have included patent sales, patent licensing, and patent divestitures.\r\n\r\nIn previous experience, Jeri spent eight years at Russell Investments, where she was instrumental in building Russell Indexes from $3M to $300M in revenues while significantly diversifying their business. Her roles at Russell included: Global Head of Strategic Partnerships, cultivating “smart beta” through global partners, launching new investment strategies, and attracting institutional assets; Head of Sales for EMEA, leading cross-functional growth throughout the region; and Director of Sales in the US, leading her team to unprecedented levels in margins, revenues, and retention. Her career began with a decade in sales at Xerox where she led the successful launch of their first e­Commerce initiative and held several sales and senior executive roles within the organization.\r\n\r\nJeri is also the Founder of The Lion’s Den Seattle, a partnership created with celebrity chef Tom Douglas to build community, create jobs, and cultivate mentoring opportunities across the Seattle landscape.\r\n\r\nJeri holds a Bachelor of Arts Degree from Boston University and has earned several financial designations including NASD/FINRA Series 7, 63 and 65.\r\n\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2933\" name=\"Shruti Kapoor\" job=\"Director, Business Development, India\" description=\"Shruti heads IDF business development in India wherein she interacts closely with inventors and research institutes looking for the next game-changing technology. She is also on the lookout for businesses and commercial entities that can be customers or partners for adopting these technologies and bringing them to the market.\r\n\r\nShruti brings a mix of finance, business and technology experience to this role. Prior to joining Intellectual Ventures, she was with Morgan Stanley in Singapore where she worked across several industry sectors, helping companies in Southeast Asia find new growth opportunities through acquisitions, restructuring, or raising capital. She has also been a research assistant at the National University of Singapore where she was involved in epidemiology research. Her exposure to the world of research in her role as RA and to client relationships during her Investment Banking days help her interact more effectively with potential inventors and business partners.\r\n\r\nShruti holds a Bachelor’s of Science in Life Sciences from the National University of Singapore and an MBA from the Indian Institute of Management Ahmedabad.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2956\" name=\"Dave Rosenberg\" job=\"Senior Director, IDF Start\" description=\"Dave leads the product development and commercial spin-out efforts for the Invention Development Fund at Intellectual Ventures. In this role he leads a global team of inventors, engineers, and technical professionals to conceive, develop, and bring to market new products and services.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Intellectual Ventures, Dave was CEO and founder of Nodeable, a real-time data analytics platform acquired in 2012 by mobile platform provider Appcelerator.\r\n\r\nPreviously, he was CEO and co-founder of open source middleware provider MuleSoft, CIO of financial services research firm GlassLewis and principal analyst for the Open Source Development Labs (now The Linux Foundation). He\'s held technical and marketing roles at Sprint, OmniSky, NorthPoint Communications, Lucent Technologies and Bell Labs.\r\n\r\nDave is extensively quoted and published. He contributes regularly to leading industry and business publications, including CNET, BusinessWeek, InfoWorld and The Register.\r\n\r\nDave holds a BA from Rutgers University and an MBA from Pepperdine University. He is a U.S. patent holder and an advisor to Appcelerator, DataStax, Puppet Labs, and IT Database.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1426151787824{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2928\" name=\"Erick Rabins\" job=\"Senior Director, SME Programs\" description=\"Erick is Senior Director of SME Programs and Investments, focusing on technology commercialization for the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures (IV). He leads a team of professionals to identify and drive monetization of IP for which IDF will deploy resources and capital to build a valuable, licensable intellectual property portfolio.\r\n\r\nErick’s career, which includes over two decades in senior management, has been primarily focused on high tech entrepreneurship and commercialization of early stage innovations. Prior to joining IV, he co-founded and lead the Auxin Group, a consultancy comprised of technology commercialization experts monetizing innovations on behalf of corporations and VC investors. He was a co-founder and key leader of Dentigenix, Inc., an oral health company, successfully sold to Europe’s largest dental products manufacturing company. He has also provided leadership at C3 Jian, an early stage company working to commercialize innovative oral health technologies.\r\n\r\nOther previous roles include Director of Business Operations at EDEN Bioscience during its successful $100m IPO (funding commercialization of their agri-biotech portfolio) and Managing Director of Business Development at Onconome, working on cancer diagnostics. He was a VP of Allied Minds, a VC firm spinning out start-up companies from major U.S. research institutes that also championed high-tech portfolio companies derived from leading university research.\r\n\r\nErick received a Bachelor of Science from the University of Wisconsin, a Master of Science from Western Washington University and an Associate of Risk Management from the American Insurance Institute. He has had Executive Board roles in biotechnology trade associations and participated on numerous national and international trade missions.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2958\" name=\"Scott Needham\" job=\"Senior Director, APAC Enterprises\" description=\"Scott has over 20 years’ experience in performing and managing R&amp;D and the commercialization of scientific discoveries.\r\n\r\nScott was Dux of his High school in New South Wales and invited into the BHP (now BHP-Billiton) Cadetship Program, from which he graduated with 1st class Honours in Materials Engineering and was on the Deans Merit list for the top 5% of all Engineering graduates.\r\n\r\nHe worked for BHP for 10 years in a variety of roles including Corrosion Scientist, focused on the development of novel metallic coatings, and Operations Manager in the company’s Sheet &amp; Coil and Stainless Steel Divisions, Port Kembla. After this, Scott spent several years in the United Kingdom, consulting in a Project Management capacity to various FTSE 100 organizations as well as London Underground.\r\n\r\nUpon returning to Australia, Scott completed a Master’s Degree in Management from Macquarie Graduate School of Management (MGSM) and a PhD investigating novel electrode materials and processes of manufacture for use in Lithium-ion batteries at the University of Wollongong. His thesis produced 14 international peer reviewed publications and over 1000 international citations. Scott was appointed Honorary Doctoral Fellow of the University of Wollongong in 2006, a position he currently holds.\r\n\r\nIn 2007, Scott became the Manager of Commercialization for Engineering, a joint position for the University of Wollongong and Uniquest Pty Ltd. During this time, negotiated over $15m in funding, started several companies and licensed various University technologies to global companies.\r\n\r\nScott is a graduate of the Venture Capital Executive Program at UC Berkeley (Haas Business School), and a member of the Australian Institute of Company Directors (GAICD).\r\n\r\nScott led the global acquisition team for IDFs Materials and Chemistry investments, and more recently is leading strategic deals as part of Monetization efforts in the APAC region. Scott is based in our Sydney Australia office.\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2962\" name=\"David Kraft\" job=\"Director, Sponsored Invention Services \" description=\"David heads the Sponsored Invention program for the Invention Development Fund. In this role, he promotes client engagements that integrate custom innovation with other key service offerings from IDF.\r\n\r\nPreviously, David was responsible for new business engagements throughout the APAC region, leading collaborations with partners and also supporting development of IDF’s global inventor network.\r\n\r\nDavid has worked across several industry sectors, from start-ups to Fortune 500 firms, to develop growth strategies, manage technology integrations and lead operational improvement activities. With over 15 years of experience in program and project management, he has gained deep practical knowledge regarding successful implementation of new technology, which often requires the development of new services, business models and support functions, along with market evaluation via opportunity and risk analysis. He applies this experience to help IDF customers who face similar challenges in adopting new technologies.\r\n\r\nDavid holds a Bachelor of Arts from Evergreen State College (USA), a Master in Business Administration from Griffith University (Australia) and is a Certified Project Manager via University of Washington (USA).\" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"][om_person style=\"colored\" img_size=\"260x260\" photo=\"2997\" name=\"Brad Roberts\" job=\"Director, Portfolio Management\" description=\"Brad heads invention sourcing in the Portfolio Management team with the Invention Development Fund at Intellectual Ventures. The team is responsible for managing a worldwide network of inventors and commercializers, setting portfolio strategy, coordinating development projects, and representing IDF in its licensing efforts.\r\n\r\nPreviously, Brad was responsible for starting IDF’s sourcing and licensing operations in Israel. He joined Intellectual Ventures in 2010 as Technical Assistant to the Fund’s Executive VP, helping to implement and optimize programs in global invention sourcing.\r\n\r\nBrad has a PhD from the University of Washington’s Department of Materials Science and Engineering in the synthesis and characterization of transition-metal-doped-oxide semiconductors for use in spin-based electronics. While at UW, he also completed a Technology Entrepreneurship Certificate at the Foster School of Business and earned a Washington Research Foundation Capital Gates Foundation Fellowship in Technology Commercialization.\r\n\r\nWhile President of the UW Science and Engineering Business Association, he facilitated programs to introduce technical students to the world of entrepreneurship and venture capital. Also, as an undergraduate, he was president of a ski touring club, co-founded a student-run engineering consulting business to utilize on-campus characterization tools, and established the campus chapter of the Alpha Sigma Mu materials engineering honor society.\r\n\r\nBrad\'s undergraduate internships included both the Hardware Engineering and Product Design groups at Apple, as well as Software Engineering group at Qualcomm. He is currently a member of the Engineering Advisory Board at California Polytechnic State University (Cal Poly).\r\n\r\nTogether, Brad and his wife, who were married while on a school-building trek in Nepal, have since helped raise tens of thousands of dollars for additional schools and infrastructure repairs in earthquake-damaged Nepali villages. \" readmore=\"Read Bio \"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_bottom=\"50\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042786961{margin-bottom: -40px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-color: #8ec549 !important;}\" bg_color=\"#0e73a3\" padding_top=\"50\"][vc_column width=\"3/4\" delimiter=\"vline\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">READY TO START THE CONVERSATION?</span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\" css=\".vc_custom_1440811513097{margin-top: 17px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"LET\'S TALK!\" color=\"custom\" hover_color=\"custom\" size=\"lg\" align=\"center\" shape=\"square\" button_block=\"true\" link=\"url:http%3A%2F%2Finventiondevfund.com%2Fcontact-us%2F||\" custom_color=\"#f78e18\" hover_custom_color=\"#dd9e40\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','About Us','','publish','open','open','','about','','','2015-10-14 22:15:14','2015-10-14 22:15:14','',0,'http://demo.olevmedia.net/amax/?page_id=636',0,'page','',0),(717,1,'2015-02-05 07:10:29','2015-02-05 07:10:29','<em>“Working with the Invention Development Fund (IDF), is like working with a personal trainer. IDF provides the motivation as well as intellectual environment to get the best of our team. They have challenged us to provide the solutions and supported these ideas through a thorough understanding of the intellectual property landscape.”</em>','Bill Walsh','','publish','closed','closed','','1','','','2016-01-07 23:20:16','2016-01-07 23:20:16','',0,'http://demo.olevmedia.net/amax/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=717',0,'testimonials','',0),(718,1,'2015-02-05 07:10:57','2015-02-05 07:10:57','<em>“Professional isolation is not good for the inventor’s soul. I find collaborating with other IVIN members often leads to better ideas, in fact, some of my recruits have become co-authors on inventions I’ve subsequently sold to Intellectual Ventures. For me, getting to focus on idea generation and leave the IP protection to someone else is a great opportunity to invent in realms I could not access otherwise. I credit more than half of my income and much of my success to Intellectual Ventures. There’s no other company besides IV that buys ideas from independent innovators.”</em>','Dr. Shmuel','','publish','closed','closed','','2','','','2016-02-22 19:18:49','2016-02-22 19:18:49','',0,'http://demo.olevmedia.net/amax/?post_type=testimonials&#038;p=718',0,'testimonials','',0),(1463,1,'2015-04-10 16:00:34','2015-04-10 16:00:34','','Yan Sheng','','publish','closed','closed','','bleora-torja','','','2015-08-28 00:42:08','2015-08-28 00:42:08','',0,'http://newthemes.themeple.co/vision_wp/?post_type=staff&#038;p=1463',0,'staff','',0),(1606,1,'2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','themeple_logo','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://newthemes.themeple.co/vision_wp/?post_type=themeple_fw_post&amp;p=4',0,'themeple_fw_post','',0),(1607,1,'2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','themeple_logo_for_dark_backgrounds','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://newthemes.themeple.co/vision_wp/?post_type=themeple_fw_post&amp;p=5',0,'themeple_fw_post','',0),(1608,1,'2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','themeple_favicon','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://newthemes.themeple.co/vision_wp/?post_type=themeple_fw_post&amp;p=6',0,'themeple_fw_post','',0),(1609,1,'2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','themeple_client_logo_dark_version','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-02-06 11:17:39','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://newthemes.themeple.co/vision_wp/?post_type=themeple_fw_post&amp;p=7',0,'themeple_fw_post','',0),(1670,1,'2015-08-27 23:52:43','2015-08-27 23:52:43','','IVIDF-logo-color','','inherit','open','closed','','ividf-logo-color','','','2015-08-27 23:52:43','2015-08-27 23:52:43','',1606,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/IVIDF-logo-color.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1671,1,'2015-08-27 23:52:44','2015-08-27 23:52:44','','IVIDF-logo-white','','inherit','open','closed','','ividf-logo-white','','','2015-08-27 23:52:44','2015-08-27 23:52:44','',1606,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/IVIDF-logo-white.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1756,1,'2015-08-28 00:41:40','2015-08-28 00:41:40','','Yan_Sheng_203_203_70_gra_c1_center_top','','inherit','open','closed','','yan_sheng_203_203_70_gra_c1_center_top','','','2015-08-28 00:41:40','2015-08-28 00:41:40','',1463,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Yan_Sheng_203_203_70_gra_c1_center_top.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2290,1,'2015-08-28 21:02:01','2015-08-28 21:02:01','','Case Studies','','publish','closed','closed','','portfolio','','','2016-03-09 22:44:10','2016-03-09 22:44:10','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/index.php/2015/08/28/portfolio/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2296,1,'2014-12-08 08:53:08','2014-12-08 08:53:08','[vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_color=\"#f2ede9\" padding_top=\"50\" padding_bottom=\"50\"][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">BUILDING SMART FOR THE FUTURE</h2>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">Innovative approach to creating high-rise dwellings transforms urban living spaces worldwide through sustainable, high-tech design.</h4>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row padding_top=\"50\" padding_bottom=\"50\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>INNOVATION</h2>\r\nIn 2008, Arlan Collins and Mark Woerman founded Sustainable Living Innovations LLC (SLI), a company focused on completing buildings more quickly while incorporating more sustainability and providing higher quality housing. Their team has developed a revolutionary system that delivers significant improvements over traditional construction techniques for mid- to high-rise buildings. The advanced method uses a kit of prefabricated components to improve building quality, reduce maintenance, and enable rapid completion of eco-smart living spaces.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_video link=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ickcnc2-x-I\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" bg_color=\"#f2ede9\" margin_bottom=\"-40\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2817\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1442855811186{margin-top: 50px !important;margin-bottom: 50px !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: contain !important;}\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>COLLABORATION</h2>\r\nTo support broader implementation of their new technology, CollinsWoerman/SLI teamed up with Intellectual Ventures’ Invention Development Fund. The companies are now working together in a global joint venture, Innovative Building Technologies (IBT), to protect, develop, and market the component-based building system and emergent related inventions. More specifically, they will leverage combined areas of expertise to further develop and strengthen their IP portfolio with inventions related to the core “kit-of-parts” technology and commercialize the inventions for global markets.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" fancy_edge=\"corner_down\" fancy_edge_size=\"lg\" padding_top=\"50\" padding_bottom=\"50\" fancy_edge_t_color=\"#0e73a3\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1441133988315{margin-top: 80px !important;}\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>EXPANSION</h2>\r\nGoing forward in strategic collaboration, CollinsWoerman/SLI will continue to expand the use of their technologies in North America while Intellectual Ventures pursues growth in key international markets such as China, Japan, and Viet Nam. Together, the companies will continue their pursuit of complementary innovations to make global multi-unit housing construction more efficient, affordable, and sustainable.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2816\"][/vc_column][vc_column][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1443728591503{margin-right: 35px !important;}\"]\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>“We view the partnership with IDF as essential to the growth of our company. We think what they can bring to material science and other enhancements to our technology and deliverables is going to be just fantastic.” </em></h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">— Rick Osterhout, Executive VP, SLI</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_bottom=\"50\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042786961{margin-bottom: -40px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-color: #8ec549 !important;}\" bg_color=\"#0e73a3\" padding_top=\"50\"][vc_column width=\"3/4\" delimiter=\"vline\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h1><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">READY TO START THE CONVERSATION?</span></h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/4\" css=\".vc_custom_1440811513097{margin-top: 17px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"LET\'S TALK!\" color=\"custom\" hover_color=\"custom\" size=\"lg\" align=\"center\" shape=\"square\" button_block=\"true\" link=\"url:http%3A%2F%2Finventiondevfund.com%2Fcontact-us%2F||\" custom_color=\"#f78e18\" hover_custom_color=\"#dd9e40\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','CollinsWoerman','','publish','open','closed','','collinswoerman','','','2015-10-16 20:15:51','2015-10-16 20:15:51','',0,'http://demo.olevmedia.net/amax/?post_type=portfolio&#038;p=189',29,'portfolio','',0),(2306,1,'2015-08-28 21:02:05','2015-08-28 21:02:05','','Services','','publish','closed','closed','','services','','','2016-03-09 22:44:10','2016-03-09 22:44:10','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/index.php/2015/08/28/services/',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(2338,1,'2015-08-28 21:27:52','2015-08-28 21:27:52','','logo-retina','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-retina','','','2015-08-28 21:27:52','2015-08-28 21:27:52','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/logo-retina.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2339,1,'2015-08-28 21:28:02','2015-08-28 21:28:02','','logo-white-green','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-white-green','','','2015-08-28 21:28:02','2015-08-28 21:28:02','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/logo-white-green.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2340,1,'2015-08-28 21:33:04','2015-08-28 21:33:04','','logo-black','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-black-2','','','2015-08-28 21:33:04','2015-08-28 21:33:04','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/logo-black.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2341,1,'2015-08-28 21:33:55','2015-08-28 21:33:55','','logo-black-retina','','inherit','open','closed','','logo-black-retina-2','','','2015-08-28 21:33:55','2015-08-28 21:33:55','',0,'http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/logo-black-retina.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(2351,1,'2015-08-28 22:44:11','2015-08-28 22:44:11','','Screen Shot 2015-08-27 at 11.33.28 PM','','inherit','open','closed','','screen-shot-2015-08-27-at-11-33-28-pm','','','2015-08-28 22:44:11','2015-08-28 22:44:11','',0,'http://inventiondev