vicon','','','2015-10-09 20:06:40','2015-10-09 20:06:40','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/IDF-favicon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3054,2,'2015-10-09 22:20:19','2015-10-09 22:20:19','','IDF Website','','inherit','open','closed','','idf-screen-shot-1','','','2015-10-09 22:21:19','2015-10-09 22:21:19','',68,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/IDF-Screen-Shot-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3056,2,'2015-09-24 10:00:25','2015-09-24 10:00:25','Eden Research <a href=\"http://www.edenresearch.com/html/news/press_releases/2015/24-09-15.asp\">announced today its new alliance</a> with the Invention Development Fund (IDF) to help enhance its product line of environmentally friendly and low-risk agricultural chemical products. IDF will activate its network of over 10,000 global inventors to source additional agrochemical inventions on behalf of Eden. IDF will then screen all of the invention ideas it receives from the network, and after selection by Eden, will undertake the work to turn these inventions into patent applications. IDF and Eden may also enter into separate discussions whereby Eden may license some of IDF’s existing portfolio of patents.\r\n\r\nGloucestershire, England-based <a href=\"http://www.edenresearch.com/index.asp\" target=\"_blank\">Eden</a> is an already well-established small public company focused on the development of natural microencapsulation technologies for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terpene\">terpenes</a> – organic compounds derived from the resin of certain plants, such as the pine tree. Terpenes provide natural antibacterial, antifungal, and antimicrobial qualities (and are a major component of turpentine). Terpene-derived pesticides can be used to naturally protect crops from commonly occurring plant diseases or pests, such as fungus, nematodes, mites, and powdery mildew. Terpene-derived antimicrobial products could be used in medical devices and oral surgery tools.\r\n\r\n<strong><em>But why is IDF getting into Terpenes? </em></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/BS8nKrIxGHQ\">IDF</a> has increasingly been working on and investing in innovations in the agricultural sector. This work generally falls into one of two categories: Projects that either help solve certain specific environmental problems, such as our <a href=\"https://inventiondevfund.com/portfolio-item/coffee-flour/\">Coffee Flour</a> or <a href=\"http://retracecorp.com/\">Retrace</a> projects, or innovations that help increase agricultural yields, such as our <a href=\"https://inventiondevfund.com/portfolio-item/case-study-raisio-benemilk/\">Benemilk</a>, <a href=\"http://www.intellectualventures.com/insights/archives/a-steak-in-invention\">Meat &amp; Livestock Australia </a>or <a href=\"http://www.horticulture.com.au/\">Horticulture Innovation Australia</a> projects. This newest alliance with Eden will fall into this second category and will help round out our family of environmentally friendly, yield enhancing projects. Ultimately, we think this has very positive implications for reducing world hunger, and lessening the use of environmentally harmful chemicals.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://youtu.be/BS8nKrIxGHQ[/embed]','Eden Research Announces an Alliance with IV’s Invention Development Fund to Expand its Range of Environmentally Friendly Agrochemicals','','publish','open','open','','eden','','','2015-10-16 18:40:05','2015-10-16 18:40:05','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/?p=3056',0,'post','',0),(3058,2,'2015-10-12 19:20:07','2015-10-12 19:20:07','','Eden Research','Eden Research Announces an Alliance with IDF ','inherit','open','closed','','eden1','','','2015-10-12 19:21:15','2015-10-12 19:21:15','',3056,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Eden1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(3059,2,'2015-10-12 19:22:35','2015-10-12 19:22:35','','Terpenes','','inherit','open','closed','','terpenes','','','2015-10-12 19:23:09','2015-10-12 19:23:09','',3056