33','',3159,'https://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Fun-Facts-Icons-04.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(3193,5,'2015-12-18 21:28:11','2015-12-18 21:28:11','<strong>December 17, 2015</strong> – Seoul, Korea – <a href=\"http://www.usa.lutronic.com/\">Lutronic Corporation</a>, a Korea-based company engaged in the manufacture of medical laser equipment, announced a strategic alliance with the Invention Development Fund (IDF) at Intellectual Ventures, a leading invention capital company, to expand its existing business, including its ophthalmology division.\r\n\r\nLutronic expects that its work with IDF will both strengthen its existing patent portfolio and create synergies in the development of new and innovative treatment technologies.\r\n\r\nThrough this strategic alliance, IDF will create complementary inventions or provide its own relevant patents that are helpful to Lutronic\'s ophthalmology business. IDF will also make its IP For Defense (IPFD) services available to Lutronic as it enters new areas of business.\r\n\r\nHaelyung HWANG, CEO of Lutronic commented that “Lutronic is a technology based company and currently has more than 200 Korean and international patents. Through this strategic alliance with IV, we will innovate to expand our ophthalmology business in the future.\"\r\n\r\nEdward Jung, CTO and one of the founders of IV said, “We are always on the lookout for strategically important, industry-leading companies such as Lutronic. I am confident that this project will result in groundbreaking inventions and innovations for Lutronic’s ophthalmology business. Ultimately, this alliance helps Lutronic innovate into new areas of growth.”\r\n\r\n<strong>About Intellectual Ventures and Invention Development Fund</strong>\r\n\r\nFounded in 2000, Intellectual Ventures (IV) is a privately-held invention capital company. With more than US$6 billion committed capital and more than 40,000 IP assets in active monetization programs, IV owns one of the 