rk on applied engineering and product development. Technical areas of focus will include chemistry, water resources, and food science. The new joint venture will be called Dovetail Innovation Pool GmbH and will be headquartered in Chemnitz, Germany.\r\n\r\n“At the Invention Development Fund, we always strive to work with the best partners worldwide. Having a joint venture in Germany now allows us to work closely with the Fraunhofer Institutes, one of the world’s premier applied research organizations,” said Chris Alliegro, Managing Director of the Invention Development Fund at Intellectual Ventures. “By building new product prototypes and commercialization projects with the Fraunhofer group, we aim to help further integrate the technical innovations happening in Germany with those of the rest of the world.”\r\n\r\n<strong>About the</strong><strong> Fraunhofer Institutes</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft is the leading organization for applied research in Europe. Its research activities are conducted by 67 institutes and research units at locations throughout Germany. The Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft employs a staff of 24,000, who work with an annual research budget totaling more than 2.1 billion euros. Of this sum, more than 1.8 billion euros is generated through contract research. More than 70 percent of the Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft’s contract research revenue is derived from contracts with industry and from publicly financed research projects.  International collaborations with excellent research partners and innovative companies around the world ensure direct access to regions of the greatest importance to present and future scientific progress and economic development.\r\n\r\n<strong>About the Invention Development Fund</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Invention Development Fund (IDF) was founded in 2007 as part of Intellectual Ventures. IDF is a private equity class investment fund with several hundred million dollars under management and is dedicated to investing in inventions. IDF has more than 75 employees, including PhDs, product and commercialization experts, business analysts, and licensing professionals operating worldwide. IDF also manages a network of thousands of inventors, commercialization and licensing partners residing at more than 400 companies, institutions, and universities worldwide. For more information go to <a href=\"http://www.inventiondevfund.com\">www.inventiondevfund.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>About Intellectual Ventures</strong>\r\n\r\nIntellectual Ventures is a global invention company that helps create a world in which invention can thrive through the shared commitment to research, collaboration, investment and defense of inventors’ rights. For press inquiries, please contact <a href=\"mailto:press@intven.com\">press@intven.com</a>. For all other inquiries, please contact <a href=\"mailto:info@intven.com\">info@intven.com</a> or <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/ivinvents\">follow IV on Twitter at @IVinvents</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Invention Development Fund at Intellectual Ventures to work on prototypes and commercialize innovations in cooperation with Germany’s Fraunhofer Institutes','','publish','open','open','','fraunhofer','','','2016-02-19 17:30:24','2016-02-19 17:30:24','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/?p=3365',0,'post','',0),(3366,5,'2016-02-18 00:00:43','2016-02-18 00:00:43','... This will be deleted shortly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Timing test post ...','','trash','open','open','','feb17test','','','2016-02-18 00:18:46','2016-02-18 00:18:46','',0,'https://inventiondevfund.com/?p=3366',0,'post','',0),(3368,4,'2016-03-03 22:50:10','2016-03-03 22:50:10','[vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" padding_bottom=\"-80\" margin_bottom=\"-80\"][vc_column offset=\"vc_hidden-lg vc_hidden-md vc_hidden-sm\"][vc_single_image image=\"3152\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_top=\"90\" padding_bottom=\"40\" font_color=\"#4d4d4d\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042963431{background-color: #f6f6f6 !important;}\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; text-align: center; font-family: lobster;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>Non-Thermal Pasteurization </strong></span></h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457045328751{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Non-thermal pasteurization reduces microorganisms and extends shelf-life without using heat.</h2>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">New cold pressed technologies are needed to increase throughput and shelf life while decreasing costs.</h3>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/6\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" bg_image_att=\"fixed\" padding_top=\"40\" padding_bottom=\"40\" font_color=\"#212121\" bg_image=\"3349\"][vc_column][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866622477{margin-bottom: 0px !important;border-bottom-width: 0px !important;}\"]\n<h1 class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e; font-family: lobster; font-size: 50px;\">Market <strong>Opportunity</strong></span></h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1441049736683{margin-top: -30px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/12\"][vc_separator color=\"custom\" border_width=\"3\" el_width=\"60\" accent_color=\"#7bc142\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][om_chart type=\"Bar\" labels=\"Australia, North America, W Europe, E Europe, Latin America, Africa, Asia\" data=\"Bln Liters|-1.5, -0.2, 1.5, 3, 4.5, 6.5, 10.8|#e75956\" legend=\"yes\" title=\"Projected Compound Annual Growth in Liters 2011 to 2016\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866008087{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\n<h4>Developing markets, such as Asia Pacific and Latin America, show an increased demand for juice products. In developed regions, the traditional juice market growth has slowed, but demand for cold-pressed or luxury juices is taking off.</h4>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866422168{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e; font-family: lobster; font-size: 40px;\"><b>Trends </b></span></h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456866398703{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>\n<h3>The juice market has <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>doubled in volume</strong></span> over the past decade</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3>Health trends have created a <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>new demand for luxury juices</strong></span> in markets where these products previously did not exist</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3>Developing markets demand for <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>packaged juice is on the rise</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3>Developed markets are seeing increased <span style=\"color: #ff940e;\"><strong>demand for cold-pressed juices</strong></span></h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" color=\"custom\" custom_color=\"#e83a43\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" padding_top=\"50\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3377\"][vc_column width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left; font-family: lobster;\">Learn More by Joining Our Inventor Network</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1456012756879{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"GET STARTED!\" color=\"custom\" size=\"xlg\" align=\"center\" link=\"url:https%3A%2F%2Fivin.intven.com%2Fsignup|title:IVIN%20Sign%20Up|target:%20_blank\" custom_color=\"#e83a43\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" font_color=\"#e83a43\" padding_top=\"40\" padding_bottom=\"10\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1449789126421{margin-right: -30px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456011548173{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; font-family: lobster; text-transform: capitalize;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\">Successful Non-Thermal Pasteurization Technologies Will</span></h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"3380\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1449789126421{margin-right: -30px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1456012395606{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Extend Shelf Life</strong> – 63 to 77 days minimum</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Have Low Regulation</strong> – New tech should be GRAS (Generally Recognized As Safe)</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Generate Consumer Acceptance</strong> – Must maintain a clean label and consumers must perceive it to be healthy</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Cost Less</strong> – Equipment and operating costs must be lower than current technology</h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1457044305122{padding-left: 25px !important;}\"]\n<h3></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Reduce Micro-organisms</strong> – Must achieve &gt;5-log reduction in pathogenic and spoilage micro-organism load</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Have a High Processing Rate</strong> – Prefer at least 25 kilo-liters/hour</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Consider Packaging</strong> – Advantageous if the product can be sterilized in its packaging</h3>\n</li>\n	<li>\n<h3><strong>Maintain Low Heat</strong> – Temperature of the food cannot exceed 24<sup>o </sup>C</h3>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" color=\"custom\" custom_color=\"#7bc142\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3378\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1456012491129{margin-top: 20px !important;}\"][vc_single_image image=\"3381\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 50px; font-family: lobster;\">Current Technology is Lacking</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_toggle title=\"Dense Phase Carbon Dioxide (DPCD) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310068421-07c427ac-7074\"]\n\nThe rapid decompression of carbon dioxide from a pressure of 500lbs/in<sup>2</sup> to ambient pressure. This is milder and lower pressure than HPP. Current limitations are low solubility in strong polar substances and poor selectively of some solutes.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Bacteriocins and Antimicrobial Ingredients \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310060557-25073fdb-f11c\"]\n\nBiologically active peptides that inhibit the growth of spoilage or pathogenic bacteria. Current limitations with the range of bacteria they can inhibit.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"High Pressure Processing (HPP) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310079465-7c8cc558-987d\"]\n\nUses hydrostatic pressures to inactivate micro-organisms with minimal heating. Current limitations are high capital costs and low throughput.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Light (PL) and UV light \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310031416-54e74c30-6b2d\"]\n\nPulsed white light inactivates vegetative cells and spores on the surfaces of foods. Current limitations are in fluid foods where the micro-organisms are located far from the UV source and don’t receive photon contact because the fluid layer absorbs it.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Electric Field (PEF)\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310042702-f1fceb8a-eb11\"]\n\nHigh Voltage pulses reduce micro-organisms. PEF is limited to the types and viscosity of foods.  Liquid foods with small particles and the presence of bubbles diminish efficacy.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Ozone/Cold Plasma \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310050840-9bb9e08b-7a2d\"]\n\nOzone (O3) applied to food is highly reactive and causes deactivation of micro-organisms. Current limitations are significant loss of color pigment, and high oxidization potential that degrades organic compounds.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Enzymes\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455309940384-181c3325-aa8c\"]\n\nEnzymes are purified from microbial cells then added to foods. Current limitations are the cost of the enzymes, and in some products they must be inactivated or removed after processing.\n\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" bg_image_att=\"parallax_down\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" padding_top=\"40\" bg_image=\"3385\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1455312071756{margin-bottom: -30px !important;background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.01) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;*background-color: rgb(0,0,0) !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; font-family: lobster; text-transform: capitalize; text-align: center;\">Invention Suggestions</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/4\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_toggle title=\"Dense Phase Carbon Dioxide (DPCD) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311780296-6c2afb3c-6257\"]\n\nSolutions that focus on high-throughput. Commercial sized DPCD equipment with continuous operations is desired.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Bacteriocins and Antimicrobial Ingredients \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311740219-874949ed-1ca5\"]\n\nNew bacteriocins and antimicrobial ingredients that are considered GRAS and can reduce micro-organism load and be accepted by consumers.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"High Pressure Processing (HPP) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310573770-5f5fa983-25be\"]\n\nInvention solutions that allow for continuous, high volume HPP rather than batch or semi-continuous as well as those that combining HPP with other technologies (DPCD, Ultrasound, PEF or PL or UV).\n\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Light (PL) and UV light \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310572765-06a6612d-d9f8\"]\n\nTechnologies that thin or aerosolize the liquid to the extent that light can penetrate all the liquid or solutions that incorporate light during pre or post processing to augment pasteurization.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Pulsed Electric Field (PEF) \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455310574833-1be21196-f7c0\"]\n\nSolutions that resolve current limitations and include applications for liquid foods and those with small particles. Inventions for continuous, large capacity PEF equipment are desired.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Ozone/Cold Plasma \" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311822594-6f9431e6-cab8\"]\n\nBecause this technology has a tendency to destroy juices, it can’t be used during the processing stage. However during pre-processing, it has little effect on whole fruits and vegetables while reducing micro-organisms. Solutions that improve or integrate this with other technologies would be considered.\n\n[/vc_toggle][vc_toggle title=\"Enzymes\" css_animation=\"left-to-right\" el_id=\"1455311705783-152f440d-863c\"]\n\nNew enzymes that are considered GRAS and can reduce micro-organism load and be accepted by consumers.\n\n[/vc_toggle][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" padding_top=\"0\" padding_bottom=\"40\" font_color=\"#4d4d4d\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042963431{background-color: #f6f6f6 !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css_animation=\"top-to-bottom\" css_animation_delay=\"200\" css=\".vc_custom_1449100474973{margin-top: 0px !important;margin-bottom: 70px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 62px; font-family: lobster; text-transform: capitalize; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff940e;\">Why Invent With Us?</span></h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_text_separator title=\"We Promote Innovation Through A Global Community of Inventors\" color=\"custom\" border_width=\"2\" el_width=\"50\" accent_color=\"#194265\" el_class=\"reduce-margin-top\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/6\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css_animation=\"top-to-bottom\" css=\".vc_custom_1449023373109{margin-bottom: 80px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"3279\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]\n<h3 class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center; font-weight: 500;\"><span style=\"color: #194265;\">Global Community</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Collaborate with an international community of inventors</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Have your inventions evaluated and potentially licensed</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Explore new realms for invention with industry defined problems to be solved</h4>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"3278\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center; font-weight: 500;\"><span style=\"color: #194265;\">Financial Reward</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Receive upfront payments and patenting for selected inventions</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Share in profits and royalties from licensing and commercialization</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Gain opportunities for technical development funding</h4>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"3280\" alignment=\"center\"][vc_column_text]\n<h3 class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center; font-weight: 500;\"><span style=\"color: #194265;\">Focus on Inventing</span></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Ability to concentrate on research, development and the invention process</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Receive help securing patents and commercially promoting your inventions</h4>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4>Gain international exposure through our established networks</h4>\n</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][om_box border_width=\"2\" border_color=\"orange\" bg_color=\"custom\" bg_custom_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3399\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" icon_type=\"fontawesome\" icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-comment\" text_color=\"#ffffff\"]\n<h3>“The unique aspect of IDF compared to other open innovation platforms is the fact it’s a community.  It’s a community of inventors but also community with the IV staff.  So you don’t work in a vacuum.  You receive feedback all the time on what you’re writing, on what you’re doing and you interact with different stakeholders.  It helps you, as an inventor really understand what everyone is looking for.  This is a critical aspect that is lacking in other open innovation platforms.”</h3>\n- Dr. Moti Margalit, Inventor and Entrepreneur[/om_box][om_box border_width=\"2\" border_color=\"orange\" bg_color=\"custom\" bg_custom_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3396\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" icon_type=\"fontawesome\" icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-comment\" text_color=\"#ffffff\"]\n<h3>“Through our work with IDF, we’ve invented in a lot of areas that we wouldn’t traditionally do. We got involved with cosmetics and that was an area neither of us really had any background in. Now, our company has become really involved with it. Since doing this, we’ve expanded our company and taken on additional clients that were working in the cosmetics space. The work that we did with IDF really helped open up additional doors for us.”</h3>\n- Dr. Greg Phelan, Managing Partner of Seattle Polymer LLC and Chemistry Chair &amp; University Professor State University of New York [/om_box][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][om_box border_width=\"2\" border_color=\"orange\" bg_color=\"custom\" bg_custom_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3393\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" icon_type=\"fontawesome\" icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-comment\" text_color=\"#ffffff\"]\n<h3>\"IDF makes the process of inventing a lot easier.  Invention involves understanding the background, commercialization opportunities, patentability issues and the client’s needs. When I invent on subjects with IDF they’ve done a lot of the work beforehand, clarifying the industry and commercialization opportunities as well as patentability questions that I might have.  When I start on a new topic I’ve already learned a lot through IDF and can just play in the technical playground that I prefer. They help you understand exactly what the problems and opportunities are so you can bring your technical expertise and a little bit of luck. They also help filter or screen your ideas so that you only spend time working on the things with the most promise.  I prefer to be directed in those areas and work on the technical areas that I enjoy the most.”</h3>\n- Dr. Angele Sjong, Inventor and Independent Consultant[/om_box][om_box border_width=\"2\" border_color=\"orange\" bg_color=\"custom\" bg_custom_color=\"#ffffff\" bg_image=\"3394\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" icon_type=\"fontawesome\" icon_fontawesome=\"fa fa-comment\" text_color=\"#ffffff\"]\n<h3>“IDF is involved in a wide variety of sciences and that gives us a wide area or a very broad encompassing view of what is needed out there. We are able to apply our knowledge to a very diverse field – from concrete to hydraulic fracturing, dying textiles without water, manufacture of textiles without water, tissue engineering, or bioreactors. All of these things eventually get published in the form of a patent out there, so it really allows the world to see how creative we are.”</h3>\n- Dr. Brendan Carlson, Inventor and Managing Partner of\nSeattle Polymer LLC\n[/om_box][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1449608302737{margin-bottom: -50px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][om_moving_box content_type=\"icon\" icon_type=\"typicons\" icon_size=\"54px\" icon_typicons=\"typcn typcn-arrow-down\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content_no_spaces\" css=\".vc_custom_1441042786961{margin-bottom: -40px !important;padding-top: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-color: #8ec549 !important;}\" padding_top=\"-10\" font_color=\"#ffffff\" padding_bottom=\"-10\" bg_color=\"#194265\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\" delimiter=\"vline\" css=\".vc_custom_1449953324432{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;}\"][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1449616747342{margin-left: 10px !important;}\"]\n<h1 class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">GET STARTED TODAY!</h1>\n<h3 class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Join IVIN today to receive further information on this invention opportunity, or to submit your invention for consideration.</h3>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_btn title=\"SIGN UP NOW!\" color=\"custom\" size=\"xlg\" align=\"center\" link=\"url:https%3A%2F%2Fivin.intven.com%2Fsignup|title:IVIN%20Sign%20Up|target:%20_blank\" custom_color=\"#ff940e\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" css=\".vc_custom_1449953371424{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;background-color: #658dc6 !important;}\" el_class=\"question-form\"][vc_column_text]\n<h1 class=\"p1\">HAVE A QUESTION?</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][gravityform id=\"5\" ajax=\"true\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row\" bg_type=\"image\" bg_image_pos=\"cover\" padding_top=\"140\" padding_bottom=\"140\" font_color=\"#212121\" css=\".vc_custom_1441058056647{padding-top: 70px !important;padding-bottom: 70px !important;background-image: url(http://inventiondevfund.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Home-About-Background4.jpg) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\" bg_image=\"2967\"][vc_column][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1449090389402{margin-bottom: 0px !important;border-bottom-width: 0px !important;}\" el_class=\"about_us\"]\n<h1 class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\">ABOUT US</h1>\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=\".vc_custom_1441049736683{margin-top: -30px !important;}\"][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/12\"][vc_separator color=\"custom\" border_width=\"3\" el_width=\"60\" accent_color=\"#7bc142\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"5/12\"][vc_column_text]\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1450118699238{margin-top: 0px !important;border-top-width: 0px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;}\"]\n<p class=\"p2\">The Invention Development Fund was established in 2007 as a new part of the Intellectual Ventures family of Investment Funds focused on building a global inventor network. IDF invents on behalf of its many customers in a variety of industries, ranging from huge multinational food and beverage or credit card companies to startups and regional Small &amp; Medium Enterprises (SMEs). IDF cultivates working relationships with inventors worldwide through its 10,000-strong global invention network (IVIN).</p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"]\n[/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\" css=\".vc_custom_1449090664800{margin-bottom: 20px !important;}\"][vc_btn title=\"JOIN OUR INVENTOR COMMUNITY\" color=\"custom\" hover_color=\"custom\" size=\"lg\" align=\"center\" shape=\"square\" link=\"url:https%3A%2F%2Fivin.intven.com%2Fsignup||\" custom_color=\"#f78e18\" hover_custom_color=\"#dd9e40\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"