INSERT INTO `qtx_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES (25,'I\'ve been mulling over a number of ideas including (since the early 1980s) a ship design innovation that would reduce transportation costs, and significantly enhance the profitability of shipping companies. I am passionate about generating useful new ideas, and would be delighted to be a part of an ecosystem that lets me focus on my strengths, instead of on the parts of the innovation and patent value chain that have been bottlenecks (for me) in the past. Best, Imon'),(30,'I have an idea for a change to a very basic device that has remained unchanged for hundreds of years. I believe this improvement will benefit perhaps hundreds of thousands of people, making life easier for them. I have tinkered with making it happen, but haven\'t quite figured it out yet. I know that this will work, but am not mechanically inclined. Would be interested with sharing my idea for some revenue sharing. This is a simple, life altering improvement.'),(35,'I am a Mexican Inventor, with several Patents in Mexico, and a lot of Patent initiatives to apply, looking for the right Partner for two key aspects:\r\n1.- Start a US Company to have access to Fed Grants as an American Company.\r\n2. Move the inventions to the experimental lab and then to the market, to create wealth,\r\nAs a serial Inventor, I have initiatives in several fields like Power energy transmission, earthquake column design, beam design, precision liquid dispensers, heavy truck axes design, osmosis filters, irrigation systems for the native tree transplantation in order to prevent a non-reverse erosion, improving plankton CO2 capture, exercise equipment for obese and people in physical  rehabilitation, educational games, innovation process learning by repetitive practice in my Knowledge Labyrinth, and so on and on.'),(40,'Hello I have some important innovations in the field of sanitary ware and fans and others - it is very necessary and very simple (I mean, God willing, the project successful 100%) - that provide (((((enough money and an international marketing))))) The profits will be A millions of dollars to their products - iam looking for a factory or financiers. - if you have this possibility or you can provide A large factory or funded PLEASE CALL ME the Innovation its not complicated and 100 % will be success and you will see that after we make and sink to the markets a lot of factories will make it ------------------------ Clarify \\ Summary of all that we wrote: - - We will make ordinary tap and provided to each house to buy one at minimum ))) (and I expect will make more than 300 million of that product inevitably sooner or later --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- And when we have made our products hit the market, and millions of her sisters neglect Because it is the success of our product is very important and necessary for each house'),(50,'Intellectual Ventures has developed a technology that could play an essential part of a concept/invention I am interested in testing the viability of.  I would like to know if IV is interested in considering this.\r\nThe phone entry format on your webpage isn\'t accepting the number I tried to enter which is + (NZ code from USA) 64 27 4192085 but email is preferable.\r\nRegards\r\nVaughan Maybury'),(55,'Hello from Vancouver, Canada,\r\n\r\nI\'ve noticed a way to break IP owned by Intel through its acquisition of another company. Reached out to the acquired company, to Intel, and other companies but no response. \r\nPerhaps they are wracking their brains trying to figure out the gap? \r\n\r\nI\'d like to take this forward as part of a venture I am building out, a disruptive tech incubator, where we license or exit patentable tech solutions. Noticing tiny clues is what I do, but asking now before creating filings because of experience with my venture WarriorHealth CombatCare. It is simply too costly and time-consuming to breach the encirclement of a massive entity. Although, it can be fun--helping my veteran customers win by helping a giant competitor lose was incredibly satisfying [UBC/VCHRI demanded the right to show IP to patent aggregators during NDA negotiations without assured compensation or benefit, or even an explanation to take to investors; and this was unacceptable, as I wanted assured swiftness of experiments to benefit my veteran customers. And open-sourced everything instead: http://www.researchgate.net/profile/David_Huer]\r\n\r\nNevertheless, going forward, it is not something I want to repeat. Too costly.\r\n\r\nIs early partnering with a disruptive inventor/entrepreneur something that IV would contemplate?\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\n\r\nDavid Huer\r\n\r\nAbout me\r\n\r\nUnorthodox thinker/entrepreneur/operations efficiency consultant,\r\nknown for solving intractable problems by noticing the tiniest of clues.\r\n\r\nPrevious venture - WarriorHealth CombatCare\r\nDetails at https://angel.co/david-huer-01 \r\n\r\nExamples outside venturing:\r\nhttp://davehuer.com/solving-wicked-problems/\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-shaker.html (creating an \"impossible-to-make\" machined part)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-minden.html (teaching an \"impossible-to-teach\" disabled student to roll a whitewater kayak)\r\n* http://davehuer.com/bcitfolio/innoprojects/inno-spraydeck.html (solving a 6-year-old, \"impossible-to-solve\" design flaw'),(60,'Boston Engineering is comprised of about 70+ engineers, has been around for 20 years and is known for its work in the robotics world and motor-control in general.  I spoke with Jeri and am interested in exploring how we might participate.'),(65,'I am part of a group that hold three provisional patents on a video needle syringe and related micro video imager. I think the next best step would be to partner with a major medical device manufacturer. Can you be of any help please?\r\nThanks\r\nAllan'),(70,'Hi,  